<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Only Way Is Essex is back on screens once again as the show is celebrating its 10-year anniversary. </p>

<p>And Chloe Meadows looked radiant as ever as she joined Courtney Green and some of their fellow co-stars for filming in Brentwood on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The reality star, 27, opted for a laid back look for the day, donning a baby blue sleeveless top and a pair of matching denim shorts.</p>

<p>Looking good: Chloe Meadows, 27, looked radiant as ever as she joined Courtney Green and some of their fellow co-stars for filming in Brentwood on Tuesday</p>

<p>Chloe showcased her sun-kissed glow while she also sported a pair of black boots and a pair of shades.</p>

<p>Making the most of the sunshine, the beauty let her platinum blonde locks fall loose down her shoulders.</p>

<p>Courtney, 25, cut a stylish figure in a black top and a matching skirt as she caught up with her co-star during filming.</p>

<p>Courtney added height to her frame with a pair of white heels while she styled her brunette tresses into loose waves.    </p>

<p>Fashion: Courtney, 25, cut a stylish figure in a black top and a matching skirt as she caught up with her co-star during filming</p>

<p>Outfit: Chloe opted for a laid back look for the day, donning a baby blue sleeveless top and a pair of matching denim shorts </p>

<p>Fun in the sun: Chloe showcased her sun-kissed glow while she also sported a pair of black boots and a pair of shades</p>

<p>The star also wore a gold necklace with her name on it and at one point, she sported a matching sequined jacket and a top hat while laughing with her co-stars.</p>

<p>Joining the ladies for filming was Liam 'Gatsby' Blackwell, 32, who sported a cream jacket with a gold key print along with matching trousers and a black shirt.</p>

<p>James 'Diags' Bennewith, 29, opted for a casual look and wore a white T-shirt with dark, slim-fitting jeans.  </p>

<p>The 10th anniversary series was due to start filming in March 2020, but ITV bosses made the tough decision to put the production on pause due to the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

